HTMLstyleindex.jspublic3d_modelsmiscobj2obj1camera1scene1camera2scene2knowing that a web Browser cant handle more than about 8 WebGL instances, I need to change my design approach to a system that shares one renderer, one canvas, but other then that all objects manage the rest of their resources like camera, materials, and the scene.
textures and other resources are shared though, which is great for performance. scene1scene2renderercamera1renderer1camera2renderer2obj1obj2manages all shared functions and resources, loading and anything related to renderingHouses some shared functions for convenience and helps with linking files to libsuncontrollablethe user can influence the interraction with intentional actions.this canvas will detail the Object Oriented Architecture of the project filesControllablethe user can influence the interaction but through unintentional actionsdoesn't necessarily mean it's static, can be an animation or a moving model, just unchangeable through outer factorsDeprecated
